                            <comment id="13081846" author="chrislott" created="Tue, 9 Aug 2011 20:07:10 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Forgot to mention this suggestion.  I found the code in MimeTypes.java about line 260 that checks for control characters in the first block.  Perhaps this could be weighted with some rule to allow the occasional control character.  For example, if fewer than 1% of the input bytes in the first block read are controls, it might be ok to parse as plain text.  Anyhow I switched to using Tika#parse(InputStream, Metadata) with better results.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13107100" author="jukkaz" created="Sat, 17 Sep 2011 12:51:48 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Implemented in revision 1171952 by allowing text content that contains up to 2% control characters and up to 10% non-ASCII characters.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
